column1: #Text=1 . A linear oscillating motor comprising a coil ( 49\u2032 ) positioned within a laminated flux path , the flux path being formed of involute laminations split about the coil , said split cutting across the flux path .

#Text=2 , A linear oscillating motor as claimed in Claim 1 , wherein a stator ( 30\u2032 ) comprises the body ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) formed of involute laminations split about the coil housed therein .
#Text=3 . A linear oscillating motor as claimed in Claim 1 or 2 , wherein the split is a cross sectional cut .
#Text=4 . A linear oscillating motor as claimed in Claim 1 or 2 , wherein the split is a circumferential cut .
#Text=5 . A linear oscillating motor as claimed in any one of the preceding Claims , wherein the laminations have uniform thickness .
#Text=6 . A linear oscillating motor as claimed in any one of the preceding Claims , wherein the laminations of the split body are aligned .
#Text=7 . A linear oscillating motor as claimed in Claim 6 , wherein the alignment does not vary by more than 10 % of the thickness of the lamination .

#Text=8 . A method of making a linear oscillating motor stator ( 30\u2032 ) comprising the steps of : a. forming two components ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) of involute laminations ; b. placing a coil ( 48\u2032,49\u2032 ) between the said two components ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) ; and c. abutting the laminations of the two components ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) to provide a flux path .

#Text=9 . A method of making a linear oscillating motor stator claimed in Claim 8 further comprising the step of aligning the laminations of the two components ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) .

#Text=10 . A method of making a linear oscillating motor stator claimed in Claim 8 further comprising the step of forming the two components ( 52\u2032,53\u2032 ; 54\u2032,55\u2032 ) by dividing a body formed of involute laminations .

#Text=11 . A cryogenic refrigerator comprising gaseous working fluid which is alternatively compressed and expanded to cool a portion of the working fluid to cryogenic temperatures and a linear oscillating drive motor for driving a piston element in the refrigerator which acts on the working fluid in a thermodynamic refrigeration cycle , the linear oscillating drive motor being a drive motor as claimed in any one of Claims 1 to 7 .
#Text=12 . A cryogenic refrigerator as claimed in Claim 11 , wherein the linear oscillating motor is used to compress gas in a compressor .
#Text=13 . A cryogenic refrigerator as claimed in Claim 12 , wherein a stator of the linear oscillating motor of a compressor is formed of involute laminations split about the coil .
#Text=14 . A cryogenic refrigerator as claimed in Claim 11 , 12 or 13 , wherein an iron mass armature is fixed to the piston element .

#Text=15 . A cryogenic refrigerator comprising gaseous working fluid which is alternatively compressed and expanded by a compressor to cool a portion of the working fluid to cryogenic temperatures and a linear oscillating drive motor for driving a piston element in the refrigerator which acts on the working fluid in a thermodynamic refrigeration cycle , the linear oscillating drive motor comprising a stator formed of involute laminations split about a coil , said split cutting across a flux path through the laminations .
